00:14:58,008 --> 00:15:00,010
Eh, look, let's talk to him
about this record.

253
00:15:00,094 --> 00:15:02,179
Hey, no, no, we're gonna
let Marlene handle that.

254
00:15:02,263 --> 00:15:04,181
You get Oberon
to call you a cab, all right.

255
00:15:04,265 --> 00:15:05,808
Great set, Ray.

256
00:15:06,934 --> 00:15:08,143
Goss!

257
00:15:08,185 --> 00:15:10,312
Hey, daddy-o, want a smoke?

258
00:15:10,854 --> 00:15:12,856
I got some gage, fresh off the boat.

259
00:15:12,898 --> 00:15:14,358
It's clean and seedless.

260
00:15:14,441 --> 00:15:16,193
So that's how it is, huh?

261
00:15:16,402 --> 00:15:19,196
You keep me high
while they talk the business?

262
00:15:19,363 --> 00:15:21,073
I ain't the one playing you, man.

263
00:15:24,201 --> 00:15:25,494
Oberon, listen ...

264
00:15:25,786 --> 00:15:29,164
You know, Marlene and Gossie are the
ones running the game on you, Ray.

265
00:15:29,206 --> 00:15:30,291
What?

266
00:15:30,374 --> 00:15:32,877
They sliced up the pie
the first night you played.

267
00:15:32,960 --> 00:15:34,670
35 percent off the top.

268
00:15:34,753 --> 00:15:36,797
Plus Gossie's
double scale as leader.

269
00:15:37,214 --> 00:15:38,507
Leader?
If anybody's leading the band,

270
00:15:38,549 --> 00:15:40,759
I'm the one that's the leader.

271
00:15:41,051 --> 00:15:42,595
Forget the bo' humps.
You know what?

272
00:15:42,678 --> 00:15:44,013
I ... I'm ... I'm gonna go
my own way.

273
00:15:44,096 --> 00:15:45,973
Who's gonna book your gigs?

274
00:15:46,098 --> 00:15:48,017
Marlene's got you locked up.

275
00:15:48,058 --> 00:15:50,853
And she ain't gonna give up
her golden goose.

276
00:15:50,978 --> 00:15:53,689
♪ Straighten up and fly right ♪

277
00:15:53,731 --> 00:15:56,275
♪ Cool down, papa,
don't you blow your top ♪

278
00:15:56,358 --> 00:15:58,527
Hey, Ray Robinson,
you are fantastic.

279
00:15:59,445 --> 00:16:01,739
There you go. Give me some skin.

280
00:16:03,365 --> 00:16:04,450
What's that?

281
00:16:04,533 --> 00:16:05,701
Jack's card.

282
00:16:05,784 --> 00:16:07,870
I got his number at the hotel.

283
00:16:13,709 --> 00:16:15,669
Come on, Q.
It's not that complicated.

284
00:16:15,753 --> 00:16:17,046
Now let's just play it again.

285
00:16:17,129 --> 00:16:18,964
That's a B flat, C 7, scale it up,

286
00:16:19,048 --> 00:16:20,966
and triple it off the back end.

287
00:16:23,260 --> 00:16:25,429
Yeah, nigger! Yeah, that's it.

288
00:16:26,972 --> 00:16:30,059
Ray, what did I tell you
about cookin' in the dark?

289
00:16:30,100 --> 00:16:31,769
Are you tryin'
to burn the house down?

290
00:16:31,852 --> 00:16:34,396
Think about it, Marlene. Uh ... uh,
what do I need the light for?

291
00:16:34,438 --> 00:16:36,232
Well, you don't need
to be cookin' anyway.

292
00:16:36,273 --> 00:16:37,858
We brought you
takeout from Oscar's.

293
00:16:37,942 --> 00:16:38,984
Well, get your money back.

294
00:16:39,068 --> 00:16:40,402
I got fried chicken right here.

295
00:16:40,486 --> 00:16:41,779
Come on, Seven-oh, try this.

296
00:16:41,862 --> 00:16:43,364
Yeah! About time.

297
00:16:45,199 --> 00:16:47,034
Hey, that's home-cooked,
right there.

298
00:16:47,117 --> 00:16:48,244
Mmm, no, thank you.

299
00:16:48,327 --> 00:16:49,745
This chicken is the mostest, huh.

300
00:16:49,787 --> 00:16:52,081
Just needs a little hot sauce
and it'll be perfect.

301
00:16:52,122 --> 00:16:54,166
Yeah. So, what did
Jack Lauderdale have to say?

302
00:16:54,250 --> 00:16:55,834
Oh, I clocked him
comin' out the gate.

303
00:16:55,918 --> 00:16:57,169
He's a two-bit hustler.

304
00:16:57,253 --> 00:16:58,420
Oh, I see.

305
00:16:58,462 --> 00:17:01,006
Yeah, turns out the only hit
that Swing Time ever had ...

306
00:17:01,090 --> 00:17:03,259
was Open the Door, Richard,
which was a joke record.

307
00:17:03,342 --> 00:17:05,219
Uh ... uh ... uh, what about him
recordin' me?

308
00:17:05,302 --> 00:17:07,638
Oh, he'll record you,
if we pay the freight.

309
00:17:07,805 --> 00:17:09,431
Scratch a liar, find a thief.

310
00:17:10,558 --> 00:17:12,059
What's that supposed to mean?

311
00:17:12,142 --> 00:17:13,352
This.

312
00:17:14,103 --> 00:17:15,980
You see I saw
Jack Lauderdale tonight,

313
00:17:16,063 --> 00:17:18,107
and he gave me a $500
advance on my record.

314
00:17:18,148 --> 00:17:20,442
He also said he'll put me
on the road with Lowell Fulson ...

315
00:17:20,484 --> 00:17:22,027
and pay me three times
what you pay.

316
00:17:22,111 --> 00:17:23,237
Now, that's a lie!

317
00:17:23,320 --> 00:17:26,740
Hey, no way he's not gonna put some
blind man on the road. Think about it.

318
00:17:26,824 --> 00:17:28,742
I mean, you ... you need
watchin' out for.

319
00:17:28,826 --> 00:17:31,036
And he ain't got the time to
look after you the way I do.

320
00:17:31,120 --> 00:17:33,539
Is that what you've been doing,
Gossie? Watchin' out for me?

321
00:17:33,622 --> 00:17:35,457
Is that why you get
paid double what I do?

322
00:17:37,001 --> 00:17:38,168
Who told you that?

323
00:17:38,252 --> 00:17:39,295
It's true, ain't it?

324
00:17:39,378 --> 00:17:41,380
You two have been
gaming me since I got here.

325
00:17:41,463 --> 00:17:43,424
Ray, baby, listen ...
I ain't listening to you!

326
00:17:43,507 --> 00:17:45,885
Ray, I've ... I've been meaning
to talk to you about that.

327
00:17:45,968 --> 00:17:48,012
Then why aren't you talkin'?

328
00:17:50,389 --> 00:17:52,641
Um, look, Ray, Ray,
let's not do nothin' stupid.

329
00:17:52,683 --> 00:17:54,476
I might be blind,
but I ain't stupid!

330
00:17:54,518 --> 00:17:56,228
Q., get my bag from upstairs.

331
00:17:56,312 --> 00:17:57,438
- What?
- Get it!

332
00:17:57,521 --> 00:17:58,981
- Wha ... right now?
- Now.

333
00:17:59,064 --> 00:18:01,317
Ray, man, we done been
through a whole lot.

334
00:18:01,358 --> 00:18:04,111
Ray, now wait a minute.
I can explain everything.

335
00:18:04,403 --> 00:18:06,113
Think about what you're doing.

336
00:18:06,197 --> 00:18:08,032
Ray, Ray, now you're makin'
a big mistake.

337
00:18:08,115 --> 00:18:10,117
That clown is spoutin'
promises that he can't keep.

338
00:18:10,201 --> 00:18:11,952
You'd be a fool to follow him.

339
00:18:12,036 --> 00:18:13,329
Ray, Ray, we'll make a new deal!

340
00:18:13,412 --> 00:18:14,538
Whatever makes you happy!

341
00:18:14,622 --> 00:18:16,540
The deal is
you can lay the pipe now.

342
00:18:16,624 --> 00:18:20,044
You'll break your neck going down
these stairs by yourself. Hang on.

343
00:18:20,502 --> 00:18:21,545
Oh, man.

344
00:18:21,629 --> 00:18:25,382
Ray, I ain't never seen you do
nothing like that, man. Never.

345
00:18:25,466 --> 00:18:27,176
That ain't nothing, Seven-oh.

346
00:18:40,147 --> 00:18:41,982
Stop cheating, Ray.

347
00:18:42,816 --> 00:18:45,444
George, you can't catch me.
Come on.

348
00:18:45,528 --> 00:18:46,862
Aretha!

349
00:18:47,571 --> 00:18:48,864
Come on, George.

350
00:18:48,948 --> 00:18:51,450
Aretha Robinson,
have you lost your mind?

351
00:18:51,534 --> 00:18:54,828
Eula, you promised to split every
wash basket with me, fair and square!

352
00:18:54,912 --> 00:18:55,996
And I did!

353
00:18:56,080 --> 00:18:57,164
Hell, you did!

354
00:18:57,248 --> 00:18:59,333
You charge white folks
one thing and pay me another.

355
00:18:59,416 --> 00:19:00,834
Now who's gonna wash these?

356
00:19:00,918 --> 00:19:02,378
You can. Now pay me my money!

357
00:19:05,965 --> 00:19:07,967
Okay, I'm a-giving you
your two little dollars.

358
00:19:08,050 --> 00:19:10,177
But don't you be expectin'
no more work out of me!

359
00:19:10,261 --> 00:19:11,679
I got all I need out of you.

360
00:19:11,804 --> 00:19:13,264
Ray and George, come on!

361
00:19:13,305 --> 00:19:14,932
That's right.
Get out of my yard ...

362
00:19:15,015 --> 00:19:16,767
and don't y'all never come back!

363
00:19:19,687 --> 00:19:22,439
Y'all got to learn
to read and write real good,

364
00:19:22,523 --> 00:19:25,276
so you never have to work
for people like that.

365
00:19:25,359 --> 00:19:27,069
Scratch a liar, find a thief.

366
00:19:27,111 --> 00:19:28,112
Understand?

367
00:19:28,153 --> 00:19:29,321
Yes, Mama.

368
00:19:42,293 --> 00:19:44,920
Smell that, Ray.
Smell the success.

369
00:19:45,212 --> 00:19:46,630
We're in LA, man,

370
00:19:46,672 --> 00:19:48,966
the place where the Negro
comes to spread his wings.

371
00:19:49,049 --> 00:19:51,468
You ... you know, man, I know
my ears ain't deceivin' me.

372
00:19:51,510 --> 00:19:52,553
Is that Art Tatum?

373
00:19:52,636 --> 00:19:54,263
It sure is, baby.
You want to meet him?

374
00:19:54,346 --> 00:19:57,016
I ... I can't meet him.
A-Art Tatum is the most.

375
00:20:02,271 --> 00:20:06,734
So, Ray, we got to talk about
your name, man: Robinson.

376
00:20:06,817 --> 00:20:09,695
Sugar Ray got the Robinson
franchise all sewed up.

377
00:20:09,778 --> 00:20:13,449
So I'm thinkin' we go with
your middle name, Charles.

378
00:20:13,991 --> 00:20:15,367
As in, Ray Charles.

379
00:20:15,451 --> 00:20:17,161
I don't care
what you call me, man,

380
00:20:17,244 --> 00:20:19,038
just as long as my name's
on the record.

381
00:20:19,121 --> 00:20:20,497
But we're gonna toast to that.

382
00:20:20,581 --> 00:20:21,874
Hey, what's the haps, Jack?

383
00:20:21,957 --> 00:20:23,584
Oh, my goodness.
Give me some skin.

384
00:20:23,667 --> 00:20:25,711
What's up, baby?
How you doin'?

385
00:20:25,794 --> 00:20:29,381
Lowell Fulson, meet your new
piano player: Ray Charles.

386
00:20:29,465 --> 00:20:32,009
Ray Charles, the blind sensation.

387
00:20:32,092 --> 00:20:35,888
Ow! Damn! I'm gonna use that
on the album cover.

388
00:20:35,971 --> 00:20:37,389
He's really the sensation.

389
00:20:37,473 --> 00:20:39,308
I ... I love your music,
Mr. Fulson.

390
00:20:39,350 --> 00:20:40,768
Uh, the man's got taste.

391
00:20:40,851 --> 00:20:43,145
Hey, and the man ain't
been on the road ...

392
00:20:43,187 --> 00:20:45,439
with a band before,
so now you take care of him.

393
00:20:45,522 --> 00:20:46,857
Like my own brother.

394
00:20:50,444 --> 00:20:51,695
Ray.

395
00:20:52,571 --> 00:20:53,697
I'm gonna be right back.

396
00:20:53,781 --> 00:20:54,823
All right.

397
00:20:55,366 --> 00:20:57,993
Yeah, you got the one
on the left.

398
00:20:58,035 --> 00:20:59,828
Look here,
let me do the talking.

399
00:21:28,649 --> 00:21:30,150
Don't go inside that place.

400
00:21:30,234 --> 00:21:31,694
You know what Mama said.

401
00:21:31,735 --> 00:21:34,238
Go home
and don't tell Mama nothin'.

402
00:21:34,738 --> 00:21:36,115
Go, George.

403
00:21:40,578 --> 00:21:42,413
George, get out of here!

404
00:22:08,188 --> 00:22:11,025
Hey, boy, who let you in?

405
00:22:11,275 --> 00:22:13,402
You must be Aretha's son, huh?

406
00:22:13,444 --> 00:22:15,696
Yes, sir. Ray Charles Robinson.

407
00:22:16,155 --> 00:22:18,908
I've been seeing you
sneakin' around here.

408
00:22:19,241 --> 00:22:20,910
You like the piano, huh?

409
00:22:21,493 --> 00:22:23,537
Come on, you want
to learn how to play?

410
00:22:23,621 --> 00:22:24,914
Come on over here.

411
00:22:24,955 --> 00:22:26,707
Let me show you how to play.
Come on.

412
00:22:26,790 --> 00:22:29,001
I'm gonna teach you how to play.

413
00:22:29,084 --> 00:22:32,004
What we'll do, I'm gonna teach
you three notes, right?

414
00:22:32,087 --> 00:22:34,173
This is the first note,
right here.

415
00:22:35,758 --> 00:22:36,842
Play that.

416
00:22:38,135 --> 00:22:40,346
And here's the second note,
right here.

417
00:22:41,513 --> 00:22:42,765
Play that.

418
00:22:44,475 --> 00:22:46,101
Here's the third note.

419
00:22:49,146 --> 00:22:50,439
Now, here's the way it goes.

420
00:22:50,522 --> 00:22:52,107
Listen. Listen closely, now.

421
00:22:55,861 --> 00:22:57,196
Play that.

422
00:22:58,781 --> 00:23:00,115
Good!

423
00:23:01,283 --> 00:23:03,035
Try the other notes.

424
00:23:11,877 --> 00:23:13,337
Every club we hit,

425
00:23:13,420 --> 00:23:15,881
it's your responsibility
to rehearse the band.

426
00:23:16,006 --> 00:23:18,008
These are some lazy-ass bastards,

427
00:23:18,092 --> 00:23:20,386
so you gotta make sure
that they don't slough off.

428
00:23:20,803 --> 00:23:22,930
You gotta be ready
and dressed to open the show.

429
00:23:23,013 --> 00:23:25,349
Now, Lowell likes to take
a nap before he goes on.

430
00:23:25,432 --> 00:23:28,477
You just do your thing
until he feels like comin' out.

431
00:23:28,561 --> 00:23:31,480
And when Lowell's playin',
you keep the band sharp.

432
00:23:31,522 --> 00:23:32,523
Uh ... uh, just one thing.

433
00:23:32,606 --> 00:23:33,524
What?

434
00:23:33,607 --> 00:23:35,734
Did Jack tell you that
I have to be paid in singles?

435
00:23:36,863 --> 00:23:39,247
You just do your job,
you're gonna get your money.

436
00:23:39,989 --> 00:23:41,657
♪ Baby, come on, down ♪

437
00:23:41,699 --> 00:23:44,869
♪ Your daddy's
in the heart of town ♪

438
00:23:48,622 --> 00:23:50,124
♪ Come on down ♪

439
00:23:50,207 --> 00:23:53,627
♪ Your daddy's in the heart of town ♪

440
00:23:59,884 --> 00:24:02,219
How'd you get the name
Fathead anyway?

441
00:24:02,303 --> 00:24:03,804
Why do they call me Fathead?

442
00:24:03,929 --> 00:24:05,472
Nah, you don't want to hear.

443
00:24:05,556 --> 00:24:07,516
But this is what
I really want to know.

444
00:24:07,600 --> 00:24:09,685
Do any of you
fine young ladies know ...

445
00:24:09,727 --> 00:24:12,104
where we can get a nice steak
this time of night?

446
00:24:12,187 --> 00:24:15,191
You mean something big,
thick, and juicy?

447
00:24:15,274 --> 00:24:17,067
Oh, yeah, that's just what I mean.

448
00:24:18,319 --> 00:24:20,571
Fathead, where you guys
headed, man?

449
00:24:21,155 --> 00:24:23,240
I ain't babysittin' no blind cat.

450
00:24:24,241 --> 00:24:25,659
Uh, I'm sorry, Ray,

451
00:24:25,743 --> 00:24:28,454
but, uh, the law says
there's only six to a cab.

452
00:24:28,537 --> 00:24:30,539
Come on, ladies,
let's get out of here.

453
00:25:27,304 --> 00:25:29,473
♪ Everyday ♪

454
00:25:34,645 --> 00:25:38,315
♪ Everyday I have the blues ♪

455
00:25:44,822 --> 00:25:48,158
♪ Everyday, everyday ♪

456
00:25:52,496 --> 00:25:54,790
Pay up, baby!
Yeah, that's all right.

457
00:25:54,832 --> 00:25:57,126
I been shootin' craps
since I was 12 years old.

458
00:25:57,167 --> 00:25:59,753
Don't never shoot craps
on a white woman's grave.

459
00:25:59,837 --> 00:26:00,796
Why not?

460
00:26:00,880 --> 00:26:01,964
It's bad luck.

461
00:26:02,006 --> 00:26:05,426
♪ You know bad luck
and trouble, people ♪

462
00:26:08,804 --> 00:26:11,473
♪ Well, you know I had my share ♪

463
00:26:17,771 --> 00:26:19,481
That's for being late to the bus.

464
00:26:19,523 --> 00:26:21,025
Wilbur, you a low-down piece ...

465
00:26:21,108 --> 00:26:22,568
You better move on.

466
00:26:28,032 --> 00:26:30,201
Ah, Mr. One-dollar Bill.

467
00:26:31,243 --> 00:26:34,914
$5, $10, $15, $20 ...

468
00:26:36,040 --> 00:26:38,667
Now, you like to start
counting that again?

469
00:26:39,877 --> 00:26:41,712
All right, damn you.

470
00:26:44,048 --> 00:26:46,217
$284, $285 ...

471
00:26:46,300 --> 00:26:49,136
Listen, man, I ain't
no damn seein'-eye dog.

472
00:26:49,220 --> 00:26:52,640
♪ You know ain't nobody worried
about me ♪

473
00:26:54,225 --> 00:26:58,896
♪ I don't see nobody, nobody cryin' ♪

474
00:27:05,903 --> 00:27:08,364
Fathead, open up. Open up.
I got to take a leak.

475
00:27:11,367 --> 00:27:14,161
Hey, what you doing, man?
Close the door, Fat!

476
00:27:14,411 --> 00:27:16,705
Say, Ray, we'll be in here
for a little while.

477
00:27:16,747 --> 00:27:19,542
Use the women's can,
down there on your right.

478
00:27:19,625 --> 00:27:21,168
I don't want to use
the women's can.

479
00:27:21,252 --> 00:27:22,294
This way, alright.

480
00:27:42,106 --> 00:27:43,399
Oh, God!

481
00:27:44,358 --> 00:27:46,235
Say, Ray, you all right?

482
00:27:47,403 --> 00:27:49,113
Yeah, I must have slipped
on the wet.

483
00:27:49,196 --> 00:27:50,281
There's a pipe broke.

484
00:27:50,364 --> 00:27:51,907
There's water everywhere.
You see it?

485
00:27:51,991 --> 00:27:53,909
Let's go, man. Close the door.

486
00:27:53,951 --> 00:27:55,369
All right, quit playing, Ray.

487
00:27:55,452 --> 00:27:57,913
We'll be in here a while.
Now go on now!

488
00:28:05,629 --> 00:28:06,672
Where you from, Ray?

489
00:28:06,755 --> 00:28:07,965
North Florida.

490
00:28:08,382 --> 00:28:09,884
Oh, North Florida boy.

491
00:28:10,426 --> 00:28:11,594
Your people still down there?

492
00:28:11,719 --> 00:28:12,887
No.

493
00:28:14,096 --> 00:28:15,222
All right.

494
00:28:15,723 --> 00:28:17,224
Hey, uh, pardon me for askin',

495
00:28:17,308 --> 00:28:19,226
but how do you
get around so good ...

496
00:28:19,310 --> 00:28:21,186
without a cane or a dog?

497
00:28:21,979 --> 00:28:24,857
How do you get around so good
without a cane or dog?

498
00:28:25,482 --> 00:28:27,067
I'm sorry. I didn't mean to pry.

499
00:28:29,153 --> 00:28:31,238
My ears got to be my eyes, man.
Its ...

500
00:28:32,031 --> 00:28:33,282
