00:41:46,367 --> 00:41:47,868
Ahem, you know what?

759
00:41:48,369 --> 00:41:50,871
Omelet, you're all right with me.

760
00:41:51,288 --> 00:41:52,498
- Ahmet.
- Ahmet.

761
00:41:52,581 --> 00:41:53,749
What kind of name is that?

762
00:41:53,791 --> 00:41:55,042
I'm Turkish.

763
00:41:55,125 --> 00:41:56,335
Well, you know what?

764
00:41:56,418 --> 00:41:59,296
I guess Jack Lauderdale's bad
luck is my good fortune.

765
00:41:59,463 --> 00:42:02,508
I knew that Atlantic Records
was bigger than Swing Time.

766
00:42:02,591 --> 00:42:05,135
You guys do good music.
I dig Atlantic.

767
00:42:05,219 --> 00:42:06,679
You could have fooled me.

768
00:42:06,762 --> 00:42:09,431
Well, you know, I gotta keep
my eye on you city boys.

769
00:42:10,015 --> 00:42:11,851
Down home,
we call it "country dumb."

770
00:42:13,978 --> 00:42:15,813
Hey, man, it ain't Turkish.

771
00:42:20,860 --> 00:42:23,153
♪ Went to see my sweetheart ♪

772
00:42:24,071 --> 00:42:26,824
♪ Last night around about ten ♪

773
00:42:27,408 --> 00:42:30,786
♪ She said, move, sweet papa ♪

774
00:42:31,620 --> 00:42:34,123
♪ Squeeze me every now and then ♪

775
00:42:34,373 --> 00:42:36,125
What do you think?

776
00:42:36,166 --> 00:42:38,586
Man, nobody wants
another Nat King Cole.

777
00:42:39,753 --> 00:42:41,714
♪ 'Cause she sleep that way ♪

778
00:42:41,797 --> 00:42:44,800
♪ The midnight hour ♪

779
00:42:46,051 --> 00:42:48,637
♪ Has found me lonely ♪

780
00:42:49,889 --> 00:42:51,807
♪ So unhappy ♪

781
00:42:53,100 --> 00:42:54,852
♪ As I can be ♪

782
00:42:55,019 --> 00:42:57,897
Ahmet, it's just
like Charles Brown.

783
00:43:00,107 --> 00:43:02,526
Okay, I'll talk to him.

784
00:43:05,154 --> 00:43:07,990
All right, fellas, that's a cut.
That's a cut, fellas.

785
00:43:08,657 --> 00:43:09,909
Fellas!

786
00:43:09,992 --> 00:43:11,327
Band can take five.

787
00:43:11,452 --> 00:43:12,786
He just don't get it.

788
00:43:12,870 --> 00:43:15,831
You either sound original,
or you got nothin'.

789
00:43:15,956 --> 00:43:18,167
Ahmet, what'd you think of that?

790
00:43:18,292 --> 00:43:21,462
Ray, I want to tell you something,
and I don't want you to take it wrong.

791
00:43:21,545 --> 00:43:22,838
Then give it to me right.

792
00:43:22,922 --> 00:43:26,342
I signed you because I sensed
something special in you ...

793
00:43:26,383 --> 00:43:29,595
not because you sound like
Nat Cole or Charles Brown.

794
00:43:29,678 --> 00:43:31,513
I thought you like what I do.

795
00:43:31,555 --> 00:43:33,516
We ... we love the timbre
of your voice,

796
00:43:33,557 --> 00:43:35,809
we like your virtuosity,
your energy ...

797
00:43:35,893 --> 00:43:37,144
But not my music.

798
00:43:37,228 --> 00:43:38,646
Come on, man, I didn't say that.

799
00:43:39,146 --> 00:43:41,148
Ahmet, this is what I do, man.

800
00:43:41,232 --> 00:43:43,359
I gotta make a living.
This is what the people want.

801
00:43:43,442 --> 00:43:45,027
I don't know no other way.

802
00:43:45,110 --> 00:43:46,862
We got to help you find one.

803
00:43:46,904 --> 00:43:49,240
Look, let's try a little
change of pace, okay?

804
00:43:49,323 --> 00:43:50,699
You're familiar with stride piano?

805
00:43:50,783 --> 00:43:54,078
You kidding me, man? The man who I
learned the piano from is a stride player.

806
00:43:54,161 --> 00:43:57,164
Okay, I got a song.
It's called "The Mess Around".

807
00:43:57,248 --> 00:43:59,083
"The Mess Around."
Cute title. Who wrote it?

808
00:43:59,166 --> 00:44:00,543
I did.

809
00:44:00,793 --> 00:44:02,211
Ah, you wrote it.

810
00:44:02,294 --> 00:44:03,295
Yeah.

811
00:44:03,712 --> 00:44:05,047
Well, sing it to me, man.

812
00:44:05,339 --> 00:44:06,507
- Sing it?
- Yeah.

813
00:44:06,590 --> 00:44:08,217
It ain't like
I can read the lyrics.

814
00:44:08,300 --> 00:44:10,886
Okay.
Well, it's the key of G.

815
00:44:10,970 --> 00:44:12,388
Okay. Key of G.

816
00:44:13,556 --> 00:44:14,515
Uh-huh.

817
00:44:15,349 --> 00:44:16,350
Yeah.

818
00:44:16,517 --> 00:44:19,353
Yeah, but it's a kind of
Pete Johnson thing.

819
00:44:19,436 --> 00:44:20,813
Pete Johnson.

820
00:44:22,606 --> 00:44:24,275
Yeah, yeah, that's it.

821
00:44:24,400 --> 00:44:26,443
You like that?
Here we go. Two, three, four.

822
00:44:26,527 --> 00:44:29,822
♪ You can talk
about the pit barbecue ♪

823
00:44:29,905 --> 00:44:32,116
♪ The band was jumpin',
the people, too ♪

824
00:44:32,199 --> 00:44:34,201
♪ They're doin' the mess around ♪

825
00:44:35,035 --> 00:44:37,037
♪ They're doin' the mess around ♪

826
00:44:37,955 --> 00:44:39,874
♪ They're doin' the mess around ♪

827
00:44:39,957 --> 00:44:41,917
♪ Everybody doin'
the mess around ♪

828
00:44:42,001 --> 00:44:44,169
All right, that's good.
Let me take it from here.

829
00:44:44,253 --> 00:44:47,798
♪ Now this band's gonna
play from nine to one ♪

830
00:44:47,882 --> 00:44:50,467
♪ Everybody here's gonna
have some fun ♪

831
00:44:50,593 --> 00:44:52,344
♪ Doin' the mess around ♪

832
00:44:53,137 --> 00:44:55,347
♪ Ah, doin' the mess around ♪

833
00:44:56,974 --> 00:44:59,143
♪ They doin' the mess around ♪

834
00:44:59,268 --> 00:45:01,353
♪ Everybody doin'
the mess around ♪

835
00:45:03,480 --> 00:45:06,942
♪ Now you see that girl
with that diamond ring ♪

836
00:45:07,568 --> 00:45:10,362
♪ She knows
how to shake that thing ♪

837
00:45:10,821 --> 00:45:12,364
♪ Mess around ♪

838
00:45:12,948 --> 00:45:14,909
♪ I declare she can mess around ♪

839
00:45:16,493 --> 00:45:18,245
♪ Ah, mess around ♪

840
00:45:18,662 --> 00:45:20,998
♪ Everybody do the mess around ♪

841
00:45:27,087 --> 00:45:28,589
Now we got something!

842
00:45:28,672 --> 00:45:30,174
That's all right there.

843
00:45:31,675 --> 00:45:32,968
What do you think, Ahmet?

844
00:45:33,010 --> 00:45:34,053
Great, Ray!

845
00:45:34,136 --> 00:45:35,262
Unbelievable!

846
00:45:35,346 --> 00:45:36,430
Who's that?

847
00:45:37,431 --> 00:45:39,642
Ray, I want you to meet
my new partner, Jerry.

848
00:45:39,725 --> 00:45:41,268
Mr. Ray Charles, Jerry Wexler.

849
00:45:41,352 --> 00:45:42,353
Hey.

850
00:45:42,436 --> 00:45:45,481
Don't worry, Ray. I'm going to
step back, I'm gonna watch,

851
00:45:45,564 --> 00:45:47,983
I'm gonna learn how to produce
a record. I'm in awe.

852
00:45:48,025 --> 00:45:49,276
That was out of sight.

853
00:45:49,360 --> 00:45:51,153
That's some running
and riffing, man!

854
00:45:51,445 --> 00:45:53,155
Well, this'll make you shout, man.

855
00:46:01,247 --> 00:46:03,999
We're listening to that
new recording, Mess Around ...

856
00:46:04,083 --> 00:46:06,377
by Atlantic recording artist,
Ray Charles.

857
00:46:06,460 --> 00:46:09,964
And we have the gentleman
live here in the KCOH studios.

858
00:46:10,047 --> 00:46:13,092
So, Ray, when you're not making your
own music, what do you listen to?

859
00:46:13,175 --> 00:46:16,845
You know what, the fact is, King Bee,
I really and truly love gospel.

860
00:46:16,887 --> 00:46:19,807
One of my favorite groups
is from right here in Houston:

861
00:46:19,890 --> 00:46:21,725
The Cecil Shaw Singers.

862
00:46:21,934 --> 00:46:25,479
You heard it: Ray Charles endorses
Houston's own Cecil Shaw.

863
00:46:25,563 --> 00:46:27,481
We'll be playing
gospel all day Sunday ...

864
00:46:27,565 --> 00:46:29,233
but right now,
let's hear some more ...

865
00:46:29,316 --> 00:46:30,943
of that Mess Around
by Ray Charles.

866
00:46:31,026 --> 00:46:32,361
K.B., line 1.

867
00:46:34,738 --> 00:46:36,073
King Bee.

868
00:46:37,783 --> 00:46:38,784
Mmm-hmm.

869
00:46:39,785 --> 00:46:41,453
Yeah, he's right here.

870
00:46:42,079 --> 00:46:44,665
Miss Della Antwine
of the Cecil Shaw Singers.

871
00:46:48,127 --> 00:46:49,962
Hello, Miss Antwine.

872
00:46:50,379 --> 00:46:53,132
You sung tenor in
Jesus Is My Shepherd, right?

873
00:46:53,215 --> 00:46:54,425
Yes.

874
00:46:55,259 --> 00:46:57,011
How did you pick me out?

875
00:46:57,094 --> 00:47:00,055
Actually,
I ... I hear like you see.

876
00:47:00,806 --> 00:47:03,851
Like that hummingbird outside
the window, for instance.

877
00:47:10,065 --> 00:47:11,317
I can't hear her.

878
00:47:11,400 --> 00:47:12,651
You have to listen.

879
00:47:30,711 --> 00:47:31,754
Yes.

880
00:47:31,837 --> 00:47:32,838
Yeah.

881
00:47:33,130 --> 00:47:34,256
Yes, you can.

882
00:47:34,340 --> 00:47:35,382
OH-OH.

883
00:47:35,466 --> 00:47:36,425
You hear that?

884
00:47:36,508 --> 00:47:37,551
What?

885
00:47:38,302 --> 00:47:40,429
Her heart just skipped a beat.

886
00:47:42,681 --> 00:47:44,558
Oh, did you like my record?

887
00:47:44,850 --> 00:47:47,228
The one that King Bee was playin'?

888
00:47:48,646 --> 00:47:50,272
It was very nice.

889
00:47:50,523 --> 00:47:52,733
Different than the others.

890
00:47:53,317 --> 00:47:55,236
I've heard a lot of your music.

891
00:47:55,319 --> 00:47:56,862
Was it very nice, too?

892
00:47:56,946 --> 00:47:59,198
Look, Miss Antwine, if you
don't really like the record,

893
00:47:59,281 --> 00:48:02,660
you ain't got to beat around the bush
with me. I mean, my mama never did.

894
00:48:02,743 --> 00:48:05,037
It's not that I don't
enjoy your music.

895
00:48:05,120 --> 00:48:07,456
It's just that I feel
I've heard it before.

896
00:48:07,498 --> 00:48:10,042
I keep wondering what the
real Ray Charles sound like.

897
00:48:10,125 --> 00:48:11,585
Ray Charles? Who's he?

898
00:48:11,669 --> 00:48:13,587
Nobody, if you don't know.

899
00:48:13,671 --> 00:48:14,630
Huh?

900
00:48:15,464 --> 00:48:17,925
Sorry. I should have
kept my mouth shut.

901
00:48:18,008 --> 00:48:20,177
Oh, no, no.
Then you wouldn't be you.

902
00:48:21,387 --> 00:48:23,806
You know, it's not like
I haven't heard that before.

903
00:48:23,848 --> 00:48:27,184
I guess I just, uh, never
really listened, that's all.

904
00:48:29,395 --> 00:48:32,356
Ain't nobody ever put
it that sweet, I guess.

905
00:48:49,582 --> 00:48:51,500
You know what,
Miss Della Bea Antwine?

906
00:48:51,542 --> 00:48:53,669
You really are a country girl.
You know that?

907
00:48:53,752 --> 00:48:55,713
Yes.
How'd you know?

908
00:48:55,796 --> 00:48:57,840
I could tell by
the way you ordered.

909
00:48:57,923 --> 00:49:00,092
"Let me get molasses
with my cornbread."

910
00:49:01,343 --> 00:49:03,012
Were you raised on a farm?

911
00:49:03,095 --> 00:49:05,931
My mother did a little
sharecropping in Florida.

912
00:49:06,015 --> 00:49:07,474
Is she still there?

913
00:49:07,558 --> 00:49:10,394
God bless her heart, she passed
away when I went to school.

914
00:49:10,477 --> 00:49:11,979
Ray, I'm sorry.

915
00:49:12,438 --> 00:49:14,148
She never was real healthy.

916
00:49:14,231 --> 00:49:16,775
She just worked herself
to death, poor thing.

917
00:49:16,901 --> 00:49:19,653
That's why she didn't want me
carrying around no tin cup.

918
00:49:19,737 --> 00:49:21,447
The kids I went to school with,

919
00:49:21,530 --> 00:49:24,200
they were doing basket-weavin'
and wickerwork.

920
00:49:25,075 --> 00:49:27,369
But not you. Because of your gift.

921
00:49:27,494 --> 00:49:29,121
Because of my ears.

922
00:49:29,413 --> 00:49:31,332
See, I can mimic
damn near anybody,

923
00:49:31,415 --> 00:49:34,084
and I ... I ... I ... I make
a pretty decent living at it.

924
00:49:34,168 --> 00:49:36,212
It's just, if I
change my style up ...

925
00:49:36,295 --> 00:49:37,838
and people really don't dig it,

926
00:49:37,922 --> 00:49:40,174
I mean, what am I
left with, you know?

927
00:49:40,424 --> 00:49:42,760
I mean, when you're blind,
Miss Antwine,

928
00:49:42,927 --> 00:49:45,012
you ain't got that many choices.

929
00:49:46,263 --> 00:49:48,724
Seem to me like you got all
the choices in the world.

930
00:49:49,934 --> 00:49:51,727
God gave you the gift to sound ...

931
00:49:51,769 --> 00:49:54,063
like anybody you please,
even yourself.

932
00:49:55,814 --> 00:49:58,025
We're here. This is where I live.

933
00:49:59,151 --> 00:50:00,986
Well, you think
the preacher'd let me in?

934
00:50:01,070 --> 00:50:03,405
I mean, uh, I'm a sinner,
but I need a little prayer.

935
00:50:03,447 --> 00:50:05,950
His wife don't like
me having male company.

936
00:50:06,075 --> 00:50:09,203
Well, tell him there's
a soul out here that needs savin'.

937
00:50:09,954 --> 00:50:13,374
You know what, Miss Antwine,
you really got me thinkin'.

938
00:50:15,209 --> 00:50:16,669
About what?

939
00:50:16,794 --> 00:50:20,089
About my life. About my music.

940
00:50:22,216 --> 00:50:23,717
About everything.

941
00:50:25,970 --> 00:50:29,431
Ray, don't ... don't you think
we're movin' a little fast?

942
00:50:31,392 --> 00:50:33,143
Listen, I'm ... I'm gonna
go to New York ...

943
00:50:33,227 --> 00:50:35,729
for a couple of weeks,
and when I get back,

944
00:50:36,146 --> 00:50:38,607
you can take it as
slow as you want.

945
00:50:41,277 --> 00:50:43,112
All right, Mr. Charles.

946
00:50:44,488 --> 00:50:46,240
All right, Miss Antwine.

947
00:50:46,657 --> 00:50:48,284
I'll see you in a couple of weeks.

948
00:50:48,325 --> 00:50:50,369
Well, hold on, now.
Let me call you a cab.

949
00:50:50,452 --> 00:50:52,121
I got it. Three blocks up,

950
00:50:52,204 --> 00:50:54,915
left for two, right for one.

951
00:50:54,999 --> 00:50:56,709
Fifteen giant steps,

952
00:50:56,792 --> 00:50:58,711
and I'm at the
Crystal White Hotel. Hello.

953
00:51:05,968 --> 00:51:08,554
"Mess Around" was
a positive step for us, Ray.

954
00:51:08,637 --> 00:51:09,763
We're making progress.

955
00:51:09,847 --> 00:51:11,974
Oh, come on, Ahmet.
Now, you've been nice to me.

956
00:51:12,057 --> 00:51:13,809
But I haven't given
you guys any hits.

957
00:51:13,893 --> 00:51:15,436
Atlantic Records
has been good to me,

958
00:51:15,519 --> 00:51:17,229
but if you want me to do
something special,

959
00:51:17,313 --> 00:51:18,647
I'm gonna need my own band.

960
00:51:19,148 --> 00:51:22,359
Oh, man. Taking a band out on
the road costs a mint, Ray.

961
00:51:22,443 --> 00:51:25,487
I mean, even Joe Morris is struggling.
His band's had a hit record.

962
00:51:25,571 --> 00:51:27,406
But, Ahmet, listen,
I'm not Joe Morris.

963
00:51:27,489 --> 00:51:29,742
Man, you told me if I think
pennies, I get pennies.

964
00:51:29,825 --> 00:51:31,702
I'm thinking dollars, man.

965
00:51:33,037 --> 00:51:35,873
Ruth Brown's got
a tour booked in Georgia.

966
00:51:36,999 --> 00:51:38,209
She needs a band.

967
00:51:38,292 --> 00:51:39,293
I ... I'll take it.

968
00:51:39,376 --> 00:51:42,129
I could write the charts
for her, I ... I could do backup,

969
00:51:42,213 --> 00:51:44,256
and also be an openin' act.

970
00:51:47,218 --> 00:51:48,552
Okay.

971
00:51:48,677 --> 00:51:50,930
But you're going to be
financially responsible.

972
00:51:51,013 --> 00:51:52,932
You're gonna have
to make it work, Ray.

973
00:51:53,015 --> 00:51:55,518
Yeah, yeah, I'm gonna make it
do what it do, baby.

974
00:51:55,601 --> 00:51:56,977
Yeah.

975
00:52:09,114 --> 00:52:10,115
Ray!

976
00:52:10,366 --> 00:52:12,785
Miss Antwine, it's been two weeks.

977
00:52:12,868 --> 00:52:14,578
It's been three.

978
00:52:20,251 --> 00:52:22,711
Now, where's the preacher at?
And the wife?

979
00:52:22,836 --> 00:52:24,922
They in Dallas till Monday.

980
00:52:25,005 --> 00:52:26,757
Well, hallelujah!

981
00:52:36,976 --> 00:52:38,394
Della Bea.

982
00:52:39,270 --> 00:52:41,063
Kind of like a honey bee, right?

983
00:52:44,984 --> 00:52:46,652
Can I call you Bea?

984
00:52:47,653 --> 00:52:49,947
Yeah, I'd like that.

985
00:52:52,825 --> 00:52:56,662
There's only been two cats that
I ever really trusted in my life.

986
00:52:58,289 --> 00:53:01,417
There's Jeff Brown, he's going
to be my tour manager,

987
00:53:02,293 --> 00:53:04,587
Fathead Newman, my tenor man ...

988
00:53:06,797 --> 00:53:08,257
and now you.

989
00:53:15,973 --> 00:53:17,349
But you gotta do me a favor.

990
00:53:17,433 --> 00:53:19,518
Bea, you gotta
always tell me the truth.

991
00:53:19,602 --> 00:53:21,729
Oh, yeah.
Just like you did before.

992
00:53:22,605 --> 00:53:25,566
Don't feel sorry for me
just 'cause I'm blind.

993
00:53:26,692 --> 00:53:29,195
How could I pity
someone I admire?

994
00:53:34,200 --> 00:53:35,701
Can I play something for you?

995
00:53:35,784 --> 00:53:37,369
- Now?
- Yeah.

996
00:53:37,453 --> 00:53:38,579
No, Ray.

997
00:53:38,662 --> 00:53:40,581
Yeah, right now.
Right now. I'm gonna ...

998
00:53:40,664 --> 00:53:41,790
Ray!

999
00:53:45,669 --> 00:53:47,546
It's right there.
You got it.

1000
00:53:47,671 --> 00:53:48,839
Okay.

1001
00:53:48,923 --> 00:53:50,132
Yeah, yeah, this will work.

1002
00:53:51,342 --> 00:53:53,636
Now you go ahead and play.
I'm gonna close these drapes.

1003
00:53:53,719 --> 00:53:54,720
All right.

1004
00:53:54,803 --> 00:53:56,305
I don't want no
neighbors looking in.

1005
00:53:56,388 --> 00:53:57,806
♪ Well ♪

1006
00:53:58,349 --> 00:53:59,975
♪ I got a woman ♪

1007
00:54:00,976 --> 00:54:02,394
