You're a cold-ass bastard!

1881
01:36:17,819 --> 01:36:18,987
Let go of me, Jeff!

1882
01:36:19,070 --> 01:36:20,905
You're a cold-ass bastard, Ray!

1883
01:36:20,989 --> 01:36:24,492
See, he wouldn't spit on me
if my ass was on fire!

1884
01:36:24,576 --> 01:36:25,660
Damn right I wouldn't.

1885
01:36:25,743 --> 01:36:27,787
Put me down, Jeff!
Put me down! Damn it!

1886
01:36:28,163 --> 01:36:29,456
You dropped your shoe.

1887
01:36:31,499 --> 01:36:33,877
All right, come on,
let's get back to work.

1888
01:36:33,960 --> 01:36:35,753
Tom, this is
what I want you to do.

1889
01:36:35,837 --> 01:36:38,298
We'll lay my vocals down
and finish the harmony parts.

1890
01:36:38,381 --> 01:36:40,884
Uh, how're we gonna do
the harmonies, Ray?

1891
01:36:40,967 --> 01:36:42,010
You sent the girls home.

1892
01:36:42,093 --> 01:36:44,471
I know what I did with the girls.
Let me take care of that.

1893
01:36:44,512 --> 01:36:47,474
You just turn that eight-track on,
and I'll do the girls' parts myself.

1894
01:36:47,557 --> 01:36:50,477
And go out here somewhere and
find me an "Oh, Johnny" girl.

1895
01:36:50,852 --> 01:36:52,479
Uh, one minute.

1896
01:36:53,480 --> 01:36:55,064
