02:06:26,586 --> 02:06:27,670
It's awful big.

2497
02:06:27,754 --> 02:06:29,339
It sure is: 8,500 square feet.

2498
02:06:29,422 --> 02:06:31,216
Biggest house in the neighborhood.

2499
02:06:31,257 --> 02:06:33,051
So, does this meet
with your approval?

2500
02:06:33,093 --> 02:06:34,594
Man, this is a palace.

2501
02:06:34,677 --> 02:06:37,180
You think this is big? Wait
until tomorrow when you see ...

2502
02:06:37,263 --> 02:06:39,557
30,000 square feet
of RPM Incorporated.

2503
02:06:39,599 --> 02:06:41,392
Yeah, headquarters!

2504
02:06:41,434 --> 02:06:43,812
This is it, Ray.
Your brand-new recording studio.

2505
02:06:43,895 --> 02:06:45,522
Did you get everything I asked for?

2506
02:06:45,605 --> 02:06:46,856
Totally state-of-the-art.

2507
02:06:46,940 --> 02:06:50,902
Tom Dowd built an eight-track mixing
console, two recorders, the works.

2508
02:06:50,944 --> 02:06:53,363
Now, this room is bigger
than most people's houses.

2509
02:06:53,446 --> 02:06:55,865
- Got your own private bathroom
to your left. - Good.

2510
02:06:55,949 --> 02:06:58,201
Right behind you
is my adjoining office.

2511
02:06:58,284 --> 02:07:00,620
And step over to your
private bar to your left.

2512
02:07:00,703 --> 02:07:02,622
Got a bottle of Bols
right in the center.

2513
02:07:02,664 --> 02:07:04,082
You know me pretty good.

2514
02:07:04,124 --> 02:07:06,543
If you run out, shout,
I'm right next door.

2515
02:07:06,876 --> 02:07:08,211
This is nice, right here.

2516
02:07:08,294 --> 02:07:09,671
It's the house that Ray built.

2517
02:07:09,754 --> 02:07:10,797
Yes, it is.

2518
02:07:11,089 --> 02:07:12,799
♪ Born to lose ♪

2519
02:07:14,467 --> 02:07:18,138
♪ I've lived my life in vain ♪

2520
02:07:22,851 --> 02:07:24,644
Ray Junior, slow down!

2521
02:07:24,727 --> 02:07:26,604
This ain't no baseball diamond!

2522
02:07:29,065 --> 02:07:30,733
Charles residence.

2523
02:07:31,401 --> 02:07:33,027
Mr. Charles?

2524
02:07:33,236 --> 02:07:35,738
Hey, girl,
Bring that boy over here!

2525
02:07:35,822 --> 02:07:37,949
I got a hot dog with his
name on it! Come on, now.

2526
02:07:38,032 --> 02:07:39,200
Hello.

2527
02:07:39,659 --> 02:07:41,786
Uh, yes, I know who you are.

2528
02:07:43,121 --> 02:07:45,290
What? Oh, God, no.

2529
02:07:45,832 --> 02:07:46,791
Ray.

2530
02:07:46,833 --> 02:07:50,336
Yes, I'll get on a plane and
I'll be there as soon as I can.

2531
02:07:50,420 --> 02:07:51,755
What happened?

2532
02:07:53,882 --> 02:07:55,216
Margie's dead.

2533
02:07:55,592 --> 02:07:57,260
Oh, God! H-How?

2534
02:07:59,012 --> 02:08:00,513
She overdosed.

2535
02:08:03,892 --> 02:08:05,685
I didn't start her, Bea.

2536
02:08:06,853 --> 02:08:08,313
I didn't let her do dope around me.

2537
02:08:08,396 --> 02:08:10,356
I ... I just wouldn't
let that happen.

2538
02:08:10,440 --> 02:08:13,693
Yes, I'm sure, Ray.
I'm sure you set a fine example.

2539
02:08:17,864 --> 02:08:19,616
What about her baby?

2540
02:08:24,078 --> 02:08:25,371
You knew?

2541
02:08:26,081 --> 02:08:28,124
His name is Charles Wayne.

2542
02:08:28,500 --> 02:08:32,337
He was born October 1, in
New York City. He's 3 years old.

2543
02:08:33,296 --> 02:08:34,798
The baby's fine.

2544
02:08:35,715 --> 02:08:37,509
He's at her sister's.

2545
02:08:39,260 --> 02:08:41,221
All right. I'll start sending
them some money.

2546
02:08:41,304 --> 02:08:44,390
You don't have to.
I send them money every month.

2547
02:09:09,249 --> 02:09:10,875
In five minutes,
Mr. Charles will be here,

2548
02:09:10,917 --> 02:09:12,419
and he'll be ready to go.

2549
02:09:12,460 --> 02:09:14,045
Now the charts
Jeff is handing out ...

2550
02:09:14,087 --> 02:09:16,923
should be turned in
at the conclusion of ...

2551
02:09:17,340 --> 02:09:19,592
You're late, that's a $50 fine.

2552
02:09:20,135 --> 02:09:21,594
I ain't late.

2553
02:09:21,636 --> 02:09:23,721
I give them
a 10-minute grace period, Joe.

2554
02:09:23,805 --> 02:09:27,100
Five minutes after two.
He's late. He'll be charged $50.

2555
02:09:27,183 --> 02:09:29,686
What? You know what?
Where's Ray?

2556
02:09:29,769 --> 02:09:32,105
You don't have to talk to Ray,
you're talking to me.

2557
02:09:32,188 --> 02:09:36,401
I'll talk to whoever I damn well
please, and it sure as hell ain't you.

2558
02:09:36,443 --> 02:09:37,777
Jive jerk.

2559
02:09:42,532 --> 02:09:43,700
Hey, Ray,

2560
02:09:43,783 --> 02:09:47,912
this fool Joe Adams is trying
to fine me for being late.

2561
02:09:48,204 --> 02:09:49,664
What time did you get here?

2562
02:09:49,748 --> 02:09:53,752
What? Just now.
The band's still setting up.

2563
02:09:54,335 --> 02:09:55,962
- Jeff don't ...
- Look, I'm not Jeff.

2564
02:09:56,045 --> 02:09:57,797
That's a fact, Jack!

2565
02:09:58,965 --> 02:10:01,634
Ray, you said the band was my thing.

2566
02:10:01,718 --> 02:10:03,178
It is.

2567
02:10:03,261 --> 02:10:05,930
Then, Fathead,
you go on back to rehearsal.

2568
02:10:06,973 --> 02:10:08,308
Ray.

2569
02:10:08,767 --> 02:10:11,186
Ray, you know how it is,
you've been there.

2570
02:10:11,728 --> 02:10:14,063
Fathead, go on now.
Let me handle this.

2571
02:10:14,147 --> 02:10:15,857
Fathead, go on now.

2572
02:10:19,319 --> 02:10:21,404
You want to tell me what the hell
is going on, Ray?

2573
02:10:21,488 --> 02:10:23,490
I'm not doing anything
I haven't been asked to.

2574
02:10:23,573 --> 02:10:25,116
Ray's running a business.

2575
02:10:25,200 --> 02:10:28,244
He shouldn't have to waste time
hearing why people were late.

2576
02:10:28,328 --> 02:10:30,121
I'm not talking to you, Joe.

2577
02:10:30,163 --> 02:10:31,915
I'm talking to Ray.

2578
02:10:36,878 --> 02:10:39,839
Ray, now I know you think
I'm soft on the band,

2579
02:10:39,881 --> 02:10:42,258
but those cats would do
whatever I ask.

2580
02:10:42,342 --> 02:10:45,011
But If you come in here with this,
uh, "running a business" crap,

2581
02:10:45,053 --> 02:10:47,305
you're gonna lose some good people.
I'm telling you, Ray.

2582
02:10:47,347 --> 02:10:49,766
There are musicians waiting in
line to play with Ray Charles.

2583
02:10:49,849 --> 02:10:52,685
Not for long,
once they get a taste of you.

2584
02:10:53,353 --> 02:10:55,563
Ray, you're the leader, man.
Be one! Come on, now.

2585
02:10:55,647 --> 02:10:57,649
You now what Jeff, I mean
things have changed.

2586
02:10:57,690 --> 02:11:00,777
It ain't like the days when it was
seven of us on the Chitlin' Circuit.

2587
02:11:00,860 --> 02:11:04,322
I mean, if you weren't busy building
a bowling alley, you'd seen that.

2588
02:11:04,697 --> 02:11:06,533
So you know about that, huh?

2589
02:11:06,991 --> 02:11:08,910
I know about everything.

2590
02:11:09,536 --> 02:11:11,496
I'm just trying to figure out
how you did it.

2591
02:11:11,579 --> 02:11:13,206
You think
I'm stealing from you, Ray?

2592
02:11:13,289 --> 02:11:16,543
If the Shaw Agency is gonna give you
a cut of the 10% I'm given them.

2593
02:11:16,626 --> 02:11:19,587
I might as well keep the
goddamn money in my pocket.

2594
02:11:19,879 --> 02:11:22,173
Leave us alone. We need to talk.

2595
02:11:23,258 --> 02:11:24,342
Ray.

2596
02:11:24,759 --> 02:11:26,803
You can step outside, Joe.

2597
02:11:28,638 --> 02:11:30,432
I'll be in my office.

2598
02:11:35,895 --> 02:11:39,774
Ray, now I know that jealous bastard
planted that lie in your head.

2599
02:11:40,900 --> 02:11:43,403
But I have never stolen
from you, Ray, and I never will.

2600
02:11:43,445 --> 02:11:47,282
I got a small business loan, and, yeah,
Milt Shaw was giving me a little extra,

2601
02:11:47,365 --> 02:11:48,992
but I'm not a thief, Ray.

2602
02:11:49,075 --> 02:11:50,410
Then what about that, Jeff, huh?

2603
02:11:50,452 --> 02:11:54,539
A promoter swearing you did side deals
with him so you could split my overages!

2604
02:11:54,622 --> 02:11:56,499
How could you do that to me?

2605
02:11:56,583 --> 02:11:58,668
We've been through so much,
we be so like brothers.

2606
02:11:58,752 --> 02:12:00,462
You know what, Ray?

2607
02:12:01,546 --> 02:12:04,549
If we were like brothers,

2608
02:12:04,883 --> 02:12:07,302
why are you paying Joe
more than you're paying me?

2609
02:12:07,385 --> 02:12:09,763
Damn all that!
You broke my heart, man.

2610
02:12:09,804 --> 02:12:14,142
Well, you know what, Ray? You broke
mine a long goddamn time ago!

2611
02:12:14,976 --> 02:12:16,936
Well, then there it is.

2612
02:12:23,568 --> 02:12:25,195
You know something, Ray?

2613
02:12:25,278 --> 02:12:27,071
You're going to get yours one day.

2614
02:12:27,113 --> 02:12:30,950
And I pray to God that he has mercy
on your soul, you son of a bitch!

2615
02:12:38,708 --> 02:12:40,752
Everything all right, Ray?

2616
02:12:41,961 --> 02:12:44,297
How the hell do you think it is?

2617
02:12:54,974 --> 02:12:58,311
Go tell him. Go tell him!
Go, go tell him.

2618
02:12:59,896 --> 02:13:01,272
Hey, Dad. Hi, there.

2619
02:13:01,314 --> 02:13:03,358
I made the all-star team!
The game's on Thursday.

2620
02:13:03,441 --> 02:13:04,484
Oh, that's great.

2621
02:13:04,567 --> 02:13:07,320
Oh, damn! I'm not gonna be in town.
I'm gotta go on tour.

2622
02:13:07,362 --> 02:13:09,948
How about I buy you guys
new uniforms, huh?

2623
02:13:10,031 --> 02:13:12,075
Tell the coach I don't care
how much they cost.

2624
02:13:12,158 --> 02:13:13,076
Okay.

2625
02:13:13,159 --> 02:13:15,703
All right, son, you want to take
your dad's briefcase inside.

2626
02:13:15,787 --> 02:13:18,415
The plane to Montreal leaves at 11:00.
I'll pick you up at 8:30.

2627
02:13:18,498 --> 02:13:19,457
All right.

2628
02:13:19,999 --> 02:13:21,960
Did you hear what
Ray Junior said to you?

2629
02:13:22,001 --> 02:13:22,961
Yeah.

2630
02:13:23,002 --> 02:13:25,338
Do you know how much making the
all-star team means to him?

2631
02:13:25,422 --> 02:13:27,882
I know. I got things on my mind.
We had to fire Jeff.

2632
02:13:27,966 --> 02:13:28,967
What?

2633
02:13:29,008 --> 02:13:30,051
He was stealing.

2634
02:13:30,135 --> 02:13:31,219
- Jeff?
- Hmm.

2635
02:13:31,302 --> 02:13:32,595
I don't believe it.

2636
02:13:32,679 --> 02:13:34,639
Yeah, well,
we're better without him.

2637
02:13:34,764 --> 02:13:37,225
♪ My mother told me ♪

2638
02:13:42,021 --> 02:13:44,649
♪ 'Fore she passed away ♪

2639
02:13:46,192 --> 02:13:49,863
♪ Said son when I'm gone ♪

2640
02:13:50,196 --> 02:13:52,157
♪ Don't forget to pray ♪

2641
02:13:52,198 --> 02:13:54,534
♪ 'Cause there'll be hard times ♪

2642
02:13:57,078 --> 02:13:59,664
♪ Hard times ♪

2643
02:13:59,706 --> 02:14:02,625
♪ Oh, yeah, yeah ♪

2644
02:14:02,709 --> 02:14:06,337
♪ Who knows better than I ♪

2645
02:14:35,658 --> 02:14:37,076
Excuse me! Get 'em out!

2646
02:14:37,535 --> 02:14:39,204
U.S. Customs!

2647
02:14:39,287 --> 02:14:41,581
We're goanna need to see some
identification, please.

2648
02:14:41,664 --> 02:14:43,416
You just arrived from Montreal?

2649
02:14:43,458 --> 02:14:44,876
Yes. Is there a problem?

2650
02:14:44,918 --> 02:14:47,253
We were alerted there might
be drugs on this plane.

2651
02:14:47,337 --> 02:14:49,714
What? That's outrageous!
I'm going to call our lawyer.

2652
02:14:49,756 --> 02:14:52,008
No lawyers
at international checkpoints.

2653
02:14:52,092 --> 02:14:54,594
Now, we're going to have to
search everyone on this plane.

2654
02:14:54,677 --> 02:14:57,430
Mr. Charles, if you don't mind
we'd like to start with you.

2655
02:14:57,472 --> 02:14:59,349
I'd like to see your overcoat.

2656
02:14:59,432 --> 02:15:00,642
I don't mind.

2657
02:15:00,725 --> 02:15:02,102
Don't say anything, Ray.

2658
02:15:02,769 --> 02:15:03,812
What's this?

2659
02:15:05,772 --> 02:15:08,149
Ray, this isn't some judge
in Indiana.

2660
02:15:08,233 --> 02:15:10,276
It's federal.
They can charge you with smuggling ...

2661
02:15:10,360 --> 02:15:12,070
which can mean real prison time.

2662
02:15:13,363 --> 02:15:16,366
Our lawyers will do
what they can, but ...

2663
02:15:36,136 --> 02:15:37,470
Hello.

2664
02:15:39,597 --> 02:15:41,474
You can't hide out
in here forever, Ray.

2665
02:15:41,516 --> 02:15:43,351
Look, it's my house.
I'm not in prison yet.

2666
02:15:43,435 --> 02:15:44,477
No, it's my house.

2667
02:15:44,561 --> 02:15:47,439
You ain't been here more than
six days since we moved in.

2668
02:15:47,480 --> 02:15:49,566
No, Ray, no!
A needle ain't gonna solve this!

2669
02:15:49,649 --> 02:15:50,608
Get out of the way. Move!

2670
02:15:50,650 --> 02:15:52,485
Only thing
that can help you is God, Ray.

2671
02:15:52,569 --> 02:15:55,280
Don't think of God? Do you have any
idea how it feels to go blind ...

2672
02:15:55,321 --> 02:15:56,781
and still be afraid of the dark?

2673
02:15:56,823 --> 02:15:59,993
And every day, you stand pray for just
a little light, and you get nothing.

2674
02:16:00,076 --> 02:16:01,911
'Cause God don't listen
to people like me.

2675
02:16:01,995 --> 02:16:03,037
Stop talking like that.

2676
02:16:03,121 --> 02:16:05,999
As far as I'm concerned, me and
God is even and I do what I please.

2677
02:16:06,082 --> 02:16:08,126
If goddamn it, if I want
to shoot up, I shoot up.

2678
02:16:08,209 --> 02:16:10,920
Then go ahead!
But you walk out that door ...

2679
02:16:11,004 --> 02:16:13,339
and I'm doing something I should
have done a long time ago.

2680
02:16:13,423 --> 02:16:15,175
I'm taking my boys and I'll leave.

2681
02:16:15,216 --> 02:16:17,260
You're not going away.
You ... you have no place to go.

2682
02:16:17,343 --> 02:16:18,845
- No place?
- No.

2683
02:16:18,928 --> 02:16:21,014
You think I'm scared of losing this?

2684
02:16:21,097 --> 02:16:24,017
Ray, the only thing I was
ever scared of losing was you.

2685
02:16:24,100 --> 02:16:27,228
Because where was I ever gonna
find another Ray Robinson?

2686
02:16:28,730 --> 02:16:31,316
So I put up with
some terrible stuff.

2687
02:16:31,524 --> 02:16:33,359
Maybe that makes me part to blame.

2688
02:16:33,443 --> 02:16:34,778
But I ain't scared no more.

2689
02:16:34,861 --> 02:16:37,530
You know I love you and those
boys more than anything.

2690
02:16:37,614 --> 02:16:40,033
That is a damn lie
and you know it!

2691
02:16:41,576 --> 02:16:43,244
You ever look at this?

2692
02:16:43,495 --> 02:16:45,747
Really look at it, Ray!

2693
02:16:46,081 --> 02:16:49,167
Ray Charles Junior's
"Most Valuable Player."

2694
02:16:50,585 --> 02:16:52,754
He was so proud this day,

2695
02:16:53,838 --> 02:16:57,717
until you came home too loaded
to go to his banquet.

2696
02:16:57,759 --> 02:17:01,054
No! No! There is something you
love more than me and them boys,

2697
02:17:01,096 --> 02:17:03,765
more than all the women you
ever slept with on the road,

2698
02:17:03,848 --> 02:17:05,475
more than all
the dope you ever took.

2699
02:17:05,558 --> 02:17:07,894
- What are you talking about?
- Your music.

2700
02:17:09,771 --> 02:17:12,107
And if you don't stop
using that needle,

2701
02:17:12,232 --> 02:17:15,360
they're gonna take away your
music and put you in jail.

2702
02:17:19,239 --> 02:17:21,574
Is that poison
worth losing everything?

2703
02:18:03,700 --> 02:18:05,368
Mr. Charles?

2704
02:18:17,756 --> 02:18:19,257
Mr. Charles.

2705
02:18:19,924 --> 02:18:21,718
You don't have to go through this.

2706
02:18:22,594 --> 02:18:26,431
We have a substitute that can
help wean you off heroin.

2707
02:18:26,765 --> 02:18:30,977
I have to do it on my own.
I can do it. I can do it.

2708
02:18:31,686 --> 02:18:33,146
Ah. Don't touch me.

2709
02:18:36,483 --> 02:18:37,817
All right.

2710
02:18:38,318 --> 02:18:40,028
We'll do it your way.

2711
02:18:51,122 --> 02:18:52,457
Doctor?

2712
02:18:52,707 --> 02:18:55,752
Mr. Charles. Mr. Charles,
I'm coming.

2713
02:18:56,503 --> 02:18:58,213
He's got no fluids left.

2714
02:18:58,338 --> 02:19:00,090
Get an I.V. in him right away.

2715
02:19:00,507 --> 02:19:02,342
- I'll insert the needle.
- No needles.

2716
02:19:02,425 --> 02:19:04,344
Yes. It's very important.
You need this.

2717
02:19:04,427 --> 02:19:06,346
Runner, I've got a runner!

2718
02:19:07,013 --> 02:19:08,014
Whoa.

2719
02:19:09,599 --> 02:19:12,018
- Let me go. Let me go.
- Get him on the bed.

2720
02:19:12,602 --> 02:19:15,105
Put those restraints on him.

2721
02:19:15,563 --> 02:19:17,148
No needles.

2722
02:19:35,417 --> 02:19:36,876
No, no.

2723
02:19:37,877 --> 02:19:39,254
Oh.

2724
02:19:43,258 --> 02:19:45,593
George, I miss you.
I miss you, George.

2725
02:19:45,718 --> 02:19:48,054
I miss you.

2726
02:19:52,725 --> 02:19:54,060
Oh.

2727
02:20:07,240 --> 02:20:08,825
- Okay.
- Uh-oh.

2728
02:20:08,908 --> 02:20:11,202
You might be in trouble
right there, Doc.

2729
02:20:20,170 --> 02:20:22,505
Hot damn,
you whupped my ass again!

2730
02:20:22,589 --> 02:20:25,341
I — I'll tell you what, I won't
lose again the same way twice.

2731
02:20:25,425 --> 02:20:28,887
I spoke with the judge in Boston,
and he'll agree to probation.

2732
02:20:29,179 --> 02:20:31,431
He was impressed with
your attorney's arguments,

2733
02:20:31,514 --> 02:20:33,558
and he believes
you deserve one more chance.

2734
02:20:33,641 --> 02:20:35,059
Oh, that's great.

2735
02:20:35,101 --> 02:20:37,103
But you must complete
our program ...

2736
02:20:37,270 --> 02:20:39,230
